parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Cam Bearing Failure in Harley-Davidson Twin Cam Engines
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear cam bearing can cause the engine to seize, leading to a loss of control, accidents, and potentially fatal consequences.
symptoms: The engine seizes or locks up
causing the motorcycle to come to a sudden stop
potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the throttle cable can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving on busy highways or in low-visibility conditions.
symptoms: The throttle cable breaks or severs
the vehicle loses power or stalls
the accelerator pedal becomes stuck or unresponsive
the vehicle experiences sudden loss of acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A loose battery lead connection can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to a loss of power and potentially stranding the driver. This can increase the risk of accidents, especially if the vehicle stalls while in motion.
symptoms: Engine stalling or failure to start
clicking or grinding sounds when trying to start the engine.
